"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63712","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-01","<p>DFID provided International Planned Parenthood Federation (IPPF) with £9m of funding for the period 2010/11, £8.6m during 2011/12 and £8.6m during 2012/13. The United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA) was provided with £20m each year for the period 2010/11 to 2012/13.</p><p>Details of further historical funding can be found in Table 18 and 19 of the Statistics on International Development (SID) which are available in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-01T15:42:05.9316112Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63712/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63712/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63712/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-24","Developing Countries: Family Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much funding her Department has allocated to the (a) International Planned Parenthood Federation and (b) United Nations Population Fund in each year since 2009.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Mr David Amess","202028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63713","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The UK is the largest donor to the GAVI Alliance with around 32% funding share during 2011-2015. We wish to see the UK's donor share reduce and other donors share increase during the GAVI Alliance's 2016-2020 strategic period. We are lobbying other donors to contribute their fair share ahead of the next replenishment pledging event in early 2015.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-06-30T14:50:13.380806Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63713/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63713/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63713/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-24","Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that there is greater equity across governments in donations to the Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunisations.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","202200"
